---
import Footer from '../index-page/Footer.astro'
import Navigation from '../index-page/Navigation.astro'
import Hero from './Hero.astro'
---

<div class="min-h-screen transition-colors duration-300">
  <Navigation />
  <Hero />
  <div class="main-frame bg-white dark:bg-slate-950">
    <div class="sponsor-bg">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 pt-14 sm:pt-16 pb-20">
        <div class="flex justify-center w-min mx-auto gap-6 text-slate-50">
          <div class="flex-1/2 p-5 rounded-2xl bg-slate-900/55 border border-slate-700/60 shadow-sm shadow-black/10 backdrop-blur-sm">
            <div class="text-4xl font-semibold">40k+</div>
            <div class="mt-4 text-md w-max text-slate-300">monthly downloads</div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex-1/2 p-5 rounded-2xl bg-slate-900/55 border border-slate-700/60 shadow-sm shadow-black/10 backdrop-blur-sm">
            <div class="text-4xl font-semibold">23k+</div>
            <div class="mt-4 text-md w-max text-slate-300">IDE installs</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="mt-5 text-xl leading-relaxed text-slate-400/90 text-center">
          Numbers change over time. The point stays the same:
          <br />
          LikeC4 is used in the real world, and maintenance is real work.
        </p>

        <section class="section">
          <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4 space-y-6">
            <p class="section-kicker">Why it matters</p>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Why sponsor LikeC4</h2>

            <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
              <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl bg-slate-900/55 border border-slate-700/60 shadow-sm shadow-black/10 backdrop-blur-sm">
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-50 mb-2">Serious tooling, independent project</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
                  A focused Architecture-as-Code toolkit used to model and visualize complex systems without click-drag
                  theater.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl bg-slate-900/55 border border-slate-700/60 shadow-sm shadow-black/10 backdrop-blur-sm">
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-50 mb-2">High leverage for your teams</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
                  Clear diagrams, shared understanding, better reviews, smoother onboarding, and documentation that
                  stays in sync.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl bg-slate-900/55 border border-slate-700/60 shadow-sm shadow-black/10 backdrop-blur-sm">
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-50 mb-2">Built and maintained by practitioners</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
                  Sponsorship funds maintenance, performance work, releases, and integrations that keep the toolkit
                  dependable.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
          <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4 space-y-4">
            <p class="section-kicker">Where sponsorship goes</p>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">What your support makes possible</h2>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
              Sponsorship is a direct input into LikeC4 improvements, not a vague fund. It pays for the unsexy work that
              makes the sexy features safe to ship.
            </p>

            <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-300">
                <li>
                  <span class="text-cyan-400 mr-2">•</span>Core features: manual layouts, deployment views, dynamic and
                  sequence views, better layout algorithms.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <span class="text-cyan-400 mr-2">•</span>Performance and stability for large models and real world
                  architectures.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <span class="text-cyan-400 mr-2">•</span>Tooling: VS Code extension, CLI, Docker images, embedding in
                  docs and internal portals.
                </li>
              </ul>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-300">
                <li>
                  <span class="text-cyan-400 mr-2">•</span>AI and MCP friendly context so your architecture is machine
                  readable without extra work.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <span class="text-cyan-400 mr-2">•</span>Documentation, guides, and examples that teams can adopt
                  without hand-holding.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <span class="text-cyan-400 mr-2">•</span>Keeping the core open and accessible for individuals and
                  teams everywhere.
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
          <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4 space-y-6">
            <p class="section-kicker">Ways to help</p>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">How to sponsor</h2>

            <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
              <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl bg-slate-900/45 border border-slate-700/60 shadow-sm shadow-black/10">
                <div class="text-slate-50 font-semibold mb-2">Individuals</div>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
                  A small monthly sponsorship helps keep the lights on and makes releases more predictable.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl bg-slate-900/45 border border-slate-700/60 shadow-sm shadow-black/10">
                <div class="text-slate-50 font-semibold mb-2">Teams</div>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
                  Sponsor to support the tooling your team depends on and to help prioritize the work that unblocks
                  adoption.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl bg-slate-900/45 border border-slate-700/60 shadow-sm shadow-black/10">
                <div class="text-slate-50 font-semibold mb-2">Companies</div>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
                  Need an invoice, a roadmap discussion, or help integrating LikeC4? Sponsorship can include that.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3">
              <a
                class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl px-5 py-3 text-sm font-medium bg-cyan-500/90 hover:bg-cyan-500 text-slate-950"
                href="https://github.com/sponsors/likec4"
              >
                Sponsor on GitHub
              </a>
              <a
                class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl px-5 py-3 text-sm font-medium border border-slate-700/60 bg-slate-900/35 hover:bg-slate-900/70 text-slate-100"
                href="/community/"
              >
                Talk in Discord / Discussions
              </a>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-6 grid gap-3">
              <details class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-700/60 bg-slate-900/35 p-4">
                <summary class="cursor-pointer text-slate-50 font-medium">What do sponsors get?</summary>
                <div class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-300 space-y-2">
                  <p>
                    Mostly: a healthier project. Practically: faster maintenance, more predictable releases, and time to
                    tackle deep work.
                  </p>
                  <p>
                    For higher tiers: public sponsor recognition (if you want it), and a direct line for prioritizing
                    work that benefits the ecosystem.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </details>

              <details class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-700/60 bg-slate-900/35 p-4">
                <summary class="cursor-pointer text-slate-50 font-medium">
                  Can you prioritize a feature for our team?
                </summary>
                <div class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-300 space-y-2">
                  <p>
                    Yes, within reason. The best way is to open an issue with context (use-case, constraints, sample
                    model) and sponsor to fund the work.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </details>

              <details class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-700/60 bg-slate-900/35 p-4">
                <summary class="cursor-pointer text-slate-50 font-medium">
                  Does sponsorship mean LikeC4 becomes closed-source?
                </summary>
                <div class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-300 space-y-2">
                  <p>
                    No. The goal is to keep the core open and accessible. Sponsorship makes it sustainable to maintain
                    that promise.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </details>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
          <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4">
            <div class="rounded-3xl border border-slate-700/60 bg-slate-900/35 p-6 sm:p-8 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-4">
              <div>
                <div class="text-slate-50 text-lg font-semibold">Help keep LikeC4 sustainable</div>
                <div class="text-sm text-slate-300 mt-1">
                  Sponsor once, or monthly. Every bit reduces maintenance debt and increases shipping speed.
                </div>
              </div>
              <a
                class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl px-5 py-3 text-sm font-medium bg-cyan-500/90 hover:bg-cyan-500 text-slate-950"
                href="https://github.com/sponsors/likec4"
              >
                Become a sponsor
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <Footer />
</div>

<style>
.main-frame {
  .content-panel {
    border-top: none;
  }
}

